those of us who remain alive our lives are no longer our 
own he said on the tape the lives of those classmates and 
countrymen who died for democracy for freedom and for our beautiful 
motherland have melted into ours 
in a letter written after his escape yan said chinas 
political situation is in the midst of a white terror 
he said the chinese leaderships inhuman policies have not only 
intensified the peoples desire for revenge and planted the seeds of 
democracy and freedom in the hearts of more and more people they 
also hastened their demise 
wuer a freshman at beijing normal university was one of the 
top leaders of the student movement for democratic reform he also 
was one of 21 students sought by chinas government for his role in 
what the authorities called a counterrevolutionary rebellion 
yan was one of the founding members of an independent union of 
beijing intellectuals who participated actively in the protests his 
name was placed on an another government wantedlist of 
intellectuals 
chinese troops crushed the prodemocracy movement on june 34 
when they opened fire on unarmed crowds in central beijing killing 
hundreds of people 
the activist said details of the new organization had yet to be 
worked out there are currently a number of organizations in the 
united states canada france and great britain devoted to 
establishing democracy in china 
but several of them including the new yorkbased chinese 
alliance for democracy have been convulsed by internal strife 
caused by both personal and ideological clashes 
some organizations are supported by taiwans nationalist 
government while others claim to be independent 
if these groups can solve their problems western experts on 
china say they could play an important role in transforming china 
a leading chinese dissident liu binyan recently urged overseas 
chinese to send weapons prodemocracy pamphlets and money to 
underground groups on the mainland 
overseas chinese organizations and money played an important role 
in the overthrow of the qing dynasty in 1911 by sun yatsen 
sun relied on chinese money in hawaii new york san francisco 
and hong kong to fuel his rebellion against the decadent qing 
chinese students abroad also played an important role in the 
chinese communist revolution late premier zhou enlai and senior 
leader deng xiaoping both lived in france and received political 
education there other communists were schooled in moscow 
today chinese has tens of thousands of students in the west 
including about 30000 in the united states 
