the 54yearold general as saying 
syrias 40000 troops in lebanon besieged the christian enclave 
early in march to retaliate for a blockade imposed by aoun against 
illegal ports run by syrianbacked militias south of beirut 
aoun and other christian leaders accuse the syrians of failing to 
achieve a 1976 peacekeeping mandate from the 22nation arab league 
by siding with the moslems against the christians in the lebanese 
civil war 
prosyrian moslem and leftist factions say syrian troops should 
remain in lebanon until the christians agree to reform the 45year 
political system in a way that guarantees equal shares to the 
various sects in running the nations affairs 
