into the international community which has condemned south africas 
system of racial separation 
our cause is just and the doors must open we will not have to 
go crawling back we will walk in proudly and with our heads high 
said de klerk who wept when the 1500 delegates greeted him with a 
standing ovation in pretoria city hall 
a less enthusiastic ovation followed his brief tribute to botha 
who did not attend the meeting the two have had strained relations 
