repression taking place in china 
they also called for an embargo on arm sales to china and urged 
the world bank to postpone new loans to beijing the united states 
australia japan and canada have taken similar steps 
the crackdown on the movement for a freer society began on june 3 
when the army drove student protesters from tiananmen square in 
beijing since then the government has arrested more than 1800 
people and announced the executions of 27 
the eec urged the chinese government to halt the executions 
respect human rights and take into account the hopes for freedom 
and democracy deeply felt by the population 
ms li said china put down the rebellion in accordance with 
the chinese constitution and that the european countries had 
unilaterally adopted decisions jeopardizing the bilateral 
relations 
all attempts by all foreign governments or organizations to 
