<TEXT>
the legislature has voted to relax a 
napoleonicera law that forces parents to leave a portion of their 
estate to their children 
the legislation amending louisianas unique forced heirship 
law would guarantee an inheritance only to offspring who are under 
23 when a parent dies 
by that time the parents have raised and educated their 
children the bills sponsor rep sydney nelson said wednesday 
critics of the law complained it deprives people of the right to 
dispose of their estates as they see fit such as withholding an 
inheritance from a wayward son or daughter 
louisiana adheres to a civil code first adopted by france 
including forced heirship which requires parents with one child to 
leave that child at least onefourth of the estate parents with two 
or more children must leave 50 percent to them 
on tuesday the house placed routine amendments on the bill and 
gave it 6536 passage the senate on wednesday concurred in the 
amendments 2610 
the bill was sent to gov buddy roemer who is expected to sign 
it nelson said 
if we concur we will be wipping out 181 years of history 
well be wiping out equality among children warned sen oswald 
decuir he said parents could pick out a favored child and leave the 
others with nothing 
forced heirship the key word is force rep randy roach 
said during the debate what right has the state to tell parents 
theyve got to leave a certain portion of their estate to adult 
children theyve already raised and educated 
