coalition will assess the results of todays talks 
the coalitions proposals for a national unity government to 
include all political parties has run up against strong opposition 
mainly because of its insistence that a coalition politician lead 
the government 
the impasse follows inconclusive june 18 elections at which the 
coalition made up of the promoscow greek communist party and the 
eurocommunist greek left won 28 seats after receiving 13 percent of 
the vote and emerged as a power broker 
president christos sartzetakis gave the coalition a threeday 
exploratory mandate after the dominant conservatives and socialists 
failed to negotiate alliances it was the first such mandate 
received by the communists since the party was recognized officially 
in 1974 
