gen wojciech jaruzelski says the communist 
partys automatic leading role in poland already is history and 
it will never return to the monopoly rule of the past 
in an interview with the associated press jaruzelski also 
praised solidarity leader lech walesa and said poland would seek 
friendly american support but not charity during the july 
911 visit of president bush 
as to his own political plans he said he would seriously 
consider the oppositions stance before deciding whether to accept 
the new office of president to be decided by the national assembly 
before bushs visit solidarity legislators who are a minority in 
the assembly have said theyll vote against jaruzelski if as 
