the state news agency reported thursday a central committee 
plenum at which the party was expected to name its candidate would 
take place friday 
i am not striving for this office the way known and typical in 
the west i will not crawl to this post jaruzelski said 
he said political and economic changes in poland put it in the 
vanguard of east bloc reform but the opportunity for change could be 
lost if society rejects economic steps that are painful like 
every surgery that is expected to bring health 
jaruzelski party leader and president of the council of state 
discussed his eight years in power from the martiallaw period to 
the historic reforms of recent months in an interview wednesday in a 
reception room near his office in the council of ministers building 
he also answered other questions in writing 
