elections losing 99 of the 100 seats in the freely contested 
senate because voters had not yet realized the extent to which the 
party has changed its program in favor of democracy and reforms 
that is why i think that if the party will honestly 
implement its program then it will have a chance to rebuild its 
influence in society he said 
but he added the partys influence could never again be on the 
basis of monopoly 
we have become convinced that monopoly is a very unhealthy 
thing not only in the economy but also in political life he 
said 
