airlines are a reduction in its size or liquidation 
david i shapiro said at a crowded hearing that a plan by a 
chicago businessman to take over the airline in partnership with 
easterns unions and with temporary management by former defense 
secretary frank c carlucci is not viable 
carlucci and businessman joseph ritchie however told the house 
public works and transportation aviation subcommittee that their 
plan offered the only hope for restoring eastern as a major airline 
the subcommittee in calling the hearing had said its goal was 
to find a way to rebuild eastern which was the nations sixth 
largest airline prior to the march walkout of its mechanics pilots 
and flight attendants 
the panel is also examining the role of the new york bankruptcy 
court which has had authority over eastern since the airline filed 
for reorganization under bankruptcy laws after the strike 
these past months have left me with the reluctant but firm 
conviction that only two practical alternative remain in this 
case said shapiro who represents the bankruptcy court the 
first is a reorganization plan premised on a smaller eastern 
airlines the second is liquidation 
easterns management which filed for reorganization under 
bankruptcy laws after the strike has announced plans to sell of 
18 billion in assets and operate the airline at a smaller scale 
ritchies plan would add about 200 million in new debt to the 
airline and restore its full operations 
i intend to use my energies to oppose liquidation and promote 
the best reorganization plan possible said shapiro he said he is 
continuing to meet with unions to try to get them to accept the idea 
that easterns operations must be scaled down to survive 
shapiro said the ritchie plan to purchase eastern presented no 
firm offer to frank lorenzos texas air in payment for the airline 
and failed to present an operational plan that would keep the 
airline flying 
carlucci said he is still willing to act as an interim chief 
executive of the airline if ritchies offer is accepted 
this approach is the only one that has a chance of restoring 
eastern to its once proud status said carlucci who was defense 
secretary in the latter part of the reagan administration 
ritchie president of chicago research amp trading group said his 
plan would restore eastern as a major competitor in the airline 
industry it includes 100 million in new money from ritchie the 
unions and other investors and 200 million or more in new financing 
lorenzo rejected ritchies earlier unionbacked attempt to buy 
the airline along with several other offers carlucci said he had 
agreed to serve as interim chief executive officer of the airline 
because ritchies plan appeared to have the support of both 
employees and creditors 
