transportation a bank surrogates court and the city of buffalo he 
attended the university of buffalo law school 
as a hud closing agent and broker according to the federal 
audit brady 
did not turn over 97371 from the sale of six hudowned 
singlefamily houses 
did not forward to hud 12407 in rental income collected from 
tenants in a hudowned property 
overcharged hud 2460 for wire transfers sometimes 
triplebilling the agency for wires never sent 
wrote checks from the hud account either to himself or his wife 
totaling almost 44000 
according to the audit 18 checks totaling 20100 and payable to 
mrs brady were drawn from the account after bradys death the 
investigation found 
for the 18 months from april 1985 to september 1986 brady did 
not submit a single monthly accounting report to the department as 
required under his contract 
at the same time as he was shortchanging hud brady was not paid 
some 26000 in monthly management fees from the department the 
audit found he also wired the same 12500 in net sales proceeds 
twice to the us treasury and he overpaid hud several hundred 
dollars in other cases 
subtracting what hud owed brady the auditors concluded that 
brady owed the department 7297066 
