impact of mr unos geisha scandal but many institutional investors 
were still reluctant to buy any issues he said 
on wednesday major japanese newspapers reported that uno had 
expressed a desire to resign after less than a month in office 
over allegations concernin his woman problems uno denied any 
intention to resign 
also we cant expect much buying incentive among japanese 
market players before the major elections nomura added 
tokyo citizens vote sunday for their municipal council and 
elections for japans upper house of parliament are scheduled july 
23 
in currency dealings traders said the dollars fall resulted 
from selling for profittaking 
although japanese market players had little incentive to buy 
the yen they were not aggressive enough to buy the dollar beyond 
the 144 yen level either said bank of tokyo trader masafumi 
koyama thats because theyre afraid the dollar might keep rising 
again after surpassing that level 
after the currency rose beyond the 144yen level june 12 it kept 
rising and reached a close of 15130 yen on june 15 many investors 
consider 144 yen as a dividing point that determines market 
direction 
koyama said japanese investors also were generally pessimistic 
over the ruling liberal democratic partys prospects in the upcoming 
elections and were reluctant to make major moves 
the bank of japan was believed to have sold dollars to support 
the yen but neither the amount nor the intervention were confirmed 
the central bank does not comment on its foreign exchange market 
activitites 
