consumers 
subcommittee chairman james l oberstar dminn said the panel 
is concerned that the course chosen by a new york bankruptcy court 
to allow eastern to sell off assets will lead to the liquidation 
of eastern the airline filed for protection from creditors under 
bankruptcy laws after the strike began 
oberstar said the panel seeks to determine how the loss of 
eastern as a major carrier will affect service and fares in the 
markets it serves 
he said the committee will examine both ritchies and easterns 
plans the bankruptcy courts ability to consider the public 
interest and any steps the transportation department has taken to 
consider the effects of the airlines reorganization on air travel 
easterns employees and its creditors 
rep newt gingrich of georgia subcommittee member and house gop 
whip has asked transportation secretary samuel skinner to intervene 
in the bankruptcy courts proceedings 
our concern is urgent gingrich said in a letter to skinner 
last week because it appears likely eastern airlines will be sold 
off in pieces resulting in less than a fully integrated competitive 
carrier 
gingrich accused lorenzo head of texas air corp which owns 
eastern of having an interest in not building up eastern as a 
competitor to his other airline continental 
gingrich said that because no assistant attorney general for 
antitrust has yet been confirmed the bankruptcy and possible sale 
of eastern airlines is taking place without proper guidance from the 
bush administration 
