sears roebuck and co said thursday it had 
created a new management structure for its retailing headquarters 
that will eliminate at least 400 jobs and make sears stores more 
responsive to customers 
the job reductions added to cuts already made among headquarters 
management workers and in field operations staff will bring to more 
than 1600 the number of sears management jobs eliminated since the 
nations largest retailer announced its streamlining plan in march 
1988 
already 425 headquarters management workers have left and about 
800 positions have been eliminated in a corresponding reorganization 
of field operations 
the new management structure will eliminate 400 managementlevel 
jobs from the sears merchandise group said ernest arms a spokesman 
for the division 
to cut the 400 jobs sears will offer incentives to quit or 
retire to most of the 3700 management workers in the chicagobased 
retail headquarters the company said the incentives will include 
two weeks of severance pay for every year worked at sears up to 52 
weeks of pay the company said 
arms said the company expects more than 400 employees to accept 
the incentive package but if fewer do it would lay off the 
necessary number to reach 400 he said any employee laid off would 
receive the incentive package 
sears announced earlier this week that the merchandise group will 
move from the sears tower to the chicago suburb of hoffman estates 
within three years the sears tower the worlds tallest building 
has been put up for sale as part of the restructuring 
arms said the new management structure which should be in place 
by midaugust will create a vertical chain of command from 
the retail store to the group vice president for each of the 
retail groups six major business lines 
for example the manager of a stores brand central appliance and 
electronics department will no longer report to the manager of that 
store but to a district manager who is also involved solely with the 
applianceandelectronics business 
the other business lines are home fashions home improvement 
womens apparel mens and childrens apparel and automotive 
arms said the management structure would fit well with the 
store of superstores concept that sears is pursuing in the 
radical restructuring of its retail business 
what this all means is that we are becoming quicker on our 
feet more responsive to the customer able to act faster in todays 
retailing environment arms said 
in an effort to battle discount chains sears has cut prices and 
increased the number of brandname products at its stores 
in yet another departure from tradition sears announced 
wednesday it would lease space in three of its stores to 
kuppenheimer mens clothiers 
the announcement came just a month after sears said it planned to 
discontinue sales of suits and sportscoats and emphasize more casual 
clothing in its mens clothing departments 
the deal with kuppenheimer is the first time sears has contracted 
with a known apparel retailer 
the strategy is similar to the recent move by montgomery ward amp 
co to rent space in its stores to specialty outlets such as toys 
r us and rose records 
sears officials said kuppenheimer will set up shop at the sears 
store in the northridge shopping center in milwaukee and at two 
other undisclosed stores on the east coast and the midwest 
kuppenheimer is a 115store subsidiary of chicagobased hartmarx 
it primarily sells privatelabel suits sportscoats dress shirts 
slacks and neckwear 
